        "#CELL 1  Markdown Cell\n",
        "# AI-Based Recruitment Screening Lab\n",
        "\n",
        "## Lab Objective\n",
        "# The objective of this lab is to help learners understand how an AI-assisted\n",
        "# recruitment system works at a basic level by:\n",
        "\n",
        "#1. Creating a small synthetic candidate dataset with 20 rows.\n",
        "#2. Understanding candidate attributes such as skills, experience, education, and certifications.\n",
        "#3. Comparing candidate resumes with a job description.\n",
        "#4. Using TF-IDF and cosine similarity to measure resume-job matching.\n",
        "#5. Creating a simple weighted scoring model for ranking candidates.\n",
        "#6. Generating a shortlist of top candidates.\n",
        "#7. Interpreting the result from an HR decision-making perspective.\n",
        "\n",
        "## Learning Outcome\n",
        "#By the end of this lab, students will be able to:\n",
        "#Explain how recruitment data can be structured for analysis.\n",
        "#Apply basic text-based AI matching in hiring.\n",
        "#Build a simple rule-based + AI-assisted candidate ranking workflow.\n",
        "#Understand that AI supports HR decisions, but does not replace human judgment.\n"
